docs/STATUS.md:190:Remote command first is a delivery preference, not a blocking rule. If `./ns agent-next` reports `NO-COMMAND`, the next assistant response must either queue a complete command pair remotely or give exactly one minimal fallback command. The user must not be kept in an `ask-agent-to-queue-command` loop. Long ad-hoc terminal blocks are only allowed when the remote command path is unavailable or broken.
