docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:129:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:19:PR #255 added an inspect-only cockpit action selection view. `agentic-kit cockpit select` renders a numbered action list from the central cockpit action registry without executing actions. `./ns select` delegates to that command, and `./ns-menu` exposes it as a numbered entry without adding new shell execution logic.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:135:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:49:- CHANGELOG, STATUS, and handoff refresh for the unreleased v0.3.19 slice.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:139:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:70:A later full local gate run showed `221 passed` and `ruff check .` passed. The documentation gates then failed because the STATUS/HANDOFF refresh removed deterministic documentation coverage phrases. This branch now restores the required coverage phrases for policy packs, policy-pack checks, documentation coverage, post-release Zenodo verification, `agentic-kit post-release-check`, and Pattern Advisor coverage in STATUS.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:150:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:147:Important local workflow note: prefer `./ns` over bare `ns`, and prefer `.venv/bin/python -m pytest`, `.venv/bin/ruff`, and `PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/python -m agentic_project_kit.cli ...` over bare `python`, `ruff`, or `agentic-kit`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:157:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:163:Implemented on main: governed planning document `docs/planning/NO_COPY_NS_WORKFLOW_CONTROL.md`, `./ns dev` for local feature gates, and a protective `./ns go` guard for dirty feature branches when `.agentic/current_work.yaml` includes `git_pull_ff_only`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:158:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:165:Important workflow note: prefer `./ns dev` for active feature-branch local gates. Use `./ns go` for the governed workflow path only when the branch state is clean and suitable for the default workflow. Long chat-to-terminal blocks remain fallback only and must start with three separator lines and end with PASS/FAIL markers.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:160:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:173:The ./ns up PR completion workflow is now hardened for safer no-copy operation. It refuses main or dirty-branch use, checks mergeability before merge, updates main only after a successful merge, uses portable separator printing, and remains compatible with the future GUI Cockpit action model.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:163:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:191:The release workflow has been hardened against recurring deterministic failures. The important fixes are: stale dist artifacts are removed before release builds, publish waits for the asynchronous GitHub Release workflow instead of failing immediately, completed releases are verified through ./ns release-verify VERSION, and repeated release checks should no longer treat an already published version as a normal release-gate target.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:165:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:199:`./ns up` now handles two recurring workflow edge cases more deterministically: pending checks are waited on instead of causing an immediate false failure, and already merged PRs are accepted as an idempotent completion state.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:166:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:205:`./ns up` now handles no-op branches idempotently: if no PR exists and the branch has no commits ahead of main, the command reports a clean completion state instead of failing. This is part of the deterministic cleanup of recurring workflow false failures.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:167:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:211:The next implementation priority is a deterministic `./ns` slice runner that can execute recurring patch and release-cycle subtasks as a bounded batch workflow. The runner should advance automatically from one step to the next on PASS, stop or enter a defined repair path on FAIL, and treat already-reached target states idempotently instead of producing artificial failures.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:171:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:219:- Longer patch operations should be implemented through robust generated script files, not heredocs, fragile inline `python -c`, or complex shell quoting.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:172:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:223:- `./ns slice <name>` for named, bounded workflows.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:173:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:224:- Initial target workflow: `./ns slice ns-up-noop-branch-idempotence` or an equivalent first hardening slice.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:175:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:233:The ./ns workflow now includes a commit-guard helper that prevents accidental direct commits and PR attempts from main. If invoked on main, it stops with an instructional failure instead of allowing a non-PR direct-main path. This is part of the current standard-error cleanup before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:176:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:239:The deterministic `./ns` slice runner is now implemented and documented as the next workflow automation layer. It supports bounded multi-step execution, advances automatically after PASS states, stops on FAIL states, and records the intended direction toward less copy-and-paste and fewer non-semantic workflow failures.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:179:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:248:`./ns finalize-guard <branch> [marker-text]` is now available to inspect finalization branches before attempting PR creation or cleanup. Use it when a docs finalization branch may already be merged, superseded, conflicting, or effectively represented on main. This is part of the standard-error cleanup path before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:183:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:265:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is complete and merged on main. The important completed fixes are: shared `control_state` model, stop-on-fail Python slice-runner core, documented workflow control contract, target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop `./ns release-gate` when release metadata is missing, and automated `./ns release-prep` metadata updates for pyproject, package `__version__`, CITATION, CHANGELOG, README, STATUS, and CURRENT_HANDOFF. Next safe direction: use the new control model to harden dirty-evidence cleanup, finalize-guard machine-readable outcomes, and stale PR cleanup classification before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:184:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:267:Evidence-cleanup guard is merged on main via PR #316. `./ns clean-evidence` is available and `./ns up` now gives a concrete repair hint for workflow-evidence dirtiness. Next safe standard-error hardening target: make `./ns finalize-guard` return clear machine-readable outcomes such as PASS_ALREADY_ON_MAIN, PASS_NOOP_BRANCH, PASS_SUPERSEDED, FAIL_CONFLICT_RELEVANT, and FAIL_NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:185:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:269:Finalize-guard outcome classification is merged on main via PR #318. ./ns finalize-guard now reports machine-readable target states: PASS_ALREADY_ON_MAIN, PASS_NOOP_BRANCH, PASS_SUPERSEDED, PASS_NEEDS_PR, FAIL_CONFLICT_RELEVANT, and FAIL_NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW. Next safe standard-error hardening target: classify stale open PRs deterministically before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:186:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:271:PR cleanup classification is merged on main via PR #320. `./ns pr-cleanup` is available as a read-only stale/open PR classifier. It does not close PRs automatically; it provides deterministic labels so stale or superseded PR noise can be handled deliberately. Remaining v0.3.23 hardening direction: integrate the control-state vocabulary deeper into `./ns up` and release verification, then prepare the v0.3.23 release.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:187:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:273:Safe patch script helper is merged on main via PR #322. `src/agentic_project_kit/safe_patch.py` now provides reusable validation/rendering support for quote-safe generated patch scripts, with tests covering heredoc avoidance, risky inline Python rejection, prompt-marker rejection, nested shell parameter expansion rejection, and exact content preservation. Next safe direction: integrate this helper into documented slice-runner or patch-generation workflows so future terminal instructions use the checked pattern by default.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:188:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:275:v0.3.23 is fully closed: GitHub Release v0.3.23 exists, Zenodo version DOI `10.5281/zenodo.20261956` is verified, and DOI metadata is recorded on main via PR #325. Current main is a clean post-release state. Recommended next direction: start v0.3.24 only if it improves the same no-copy/GUI cockpit path; otherwise cut a new planning slice for how `./ns pr-cleanup`, `./ns finalize-guard`, `./ns clean-evidence`, release controls, and safe patch helpers should appear in the local Tkinter cockpit without enabling unsafe destructive defaults.
