docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:713:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:175:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:233:The ./ns workflow now includes a commit-guard helper that prevents accidental direct commits and PR attempts from main. If invoked on main, it stops with an instructional failure instead of allowing a non-PR direct-main path. This is part of the current standard-error cleanup before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:714:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:179:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:248:`./ns finalize-guard <branch> [marker-text]` is now available to inspect finalization branches before attempting PR creation or cleanup. Use it when a docs finalization branch may already be merged, superseded, conflicting, or effectively represented on main. This is part of the standard-error cleanup path before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
