docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:391:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:19:PR #255 added an inspect-only cockpit action selection view. `agentic-kit cockpit select` renders a numbered action list from the central cockpit action registry without executing actions. `./ns select` delegates to that command, and `./ns-menu` exposes it as a numbered entry without adding new shell execution logic.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:393:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:185:- `./ns release-verify 0.3.21` passes.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:394:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:191:The release workflow has been hardened against recurring deterministic failures. The important fixes are: stale dist artifacts are removed before release builds, publish waits for the asynchronous GitHub Release workflow instead of failing immediately, completed releases are verified through ./ns release-verify VERSION, and repeated release checks should no longer treat an already published version as a normal release-gate target.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:395:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:263:- `./ns release-verify 0.3.22` passes.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:396:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:265:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is complete and merged on main. The important completed fixes are: shared `control_state` model, stop-on-fail Python slice-runner core, documented workflow control contract, target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop `./ns release-gate` when release metadata is missing, and automated `./ns release-prep` metadata updates for pyproject, package `__version__`, CITATION, CHANGELOG, README, STATUS, and CURRENT_HANDOFF. Next safe direction: use the new control model to harden dirty-evidence cleanup, finalize-guard machine-readable outcomes, and stale PR cleanup classification before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:397:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:271:PR cleanup classification is merged on main via PR #320. `./ns pr-cleanup` is available as a read-only stale/open PR classifier. It does not close PRs automatically; it provides deterministic labels so stale or superseded PR noise can be handled deliberately. Remaining v0.3.23 hardening direction: integrate the control-state vocabulary deeper into `./ns up` and release verification, then prepare the v0.3.23 release.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:398:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:275:v0.3.23 is fully closed: GitHub Release v0.3.23 exists, Zenodo version DOI `10.5281/zenodo.20261956` is verified, and DOI metadata is recorded on main via PR #325. Current main is a clean post-release state. Recommended next direction: start v0.3.24 only if it improves the same no-copy/GUI cockpit path; otherwise cut a new planning slice for how `./ns pr-cleanup`, `./ns finalize-guard`, `./ns clean-evidence`, release controls, and safe patch helpers should appear in the local Tkinter cockpit without enabling unsafe destructive defaults.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:399:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:285:- Current slice: `feature/agent-command-inbox` adds inbox-based `./ns agent-next`; prefer one pending command pair under `.agentic/commands/inbox/` instead of transient current files.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:400:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:286:- Completed: PR #336 merged agent-next inbox mode. Preferred routine workflow is now: commit one command pair under .agentic/commands/inbox/, run ./ns agent-next locally, and use committed command-run/terminal artifacts instead of pasted terminal output.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:402:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:292:- Verified state: `319 passed`, ruff PASS, `agentic-kit check-docs` PASS, `agentic-kit doctor` PASS, and `./ns release-verify 0.3.24` PASS.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:404:docs/TEST_GATES.md:141:When changing the local cockpit, cockpit action registry, cockpit CLI adapter, `./ns cockpit` shortcuts, or `./ns-menu` cockpit entries, run unit tests plus explicit CLI smoke commands.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:406:docs/STATUS.md:31:PR #255 added an inspect-only cockpit action selection view. `agentic-kit cockpit select` renders a numbered action list from the central cockpit action registry without executing actions. `./ns select` delegates to that command, and `./ns-menu` exposes it as a numbered entry without adding new shell execution logic.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:408:docs/STATUS.md:233:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is integrated on main. The release/PR/finalization workflow now has a shared deterministic control model with machine-readable target states, a stop-on-fail slice runner core, documented control-state semantics, a target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop release-gate behavior when release metadata is missing, and automated release metadata preparation in `./ns release-prep`. This addresses the recurring standard-error class where already reached target states, retryable pending states, or failed core patches caused misleading follow-up failures.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:409:docs/STATUS.md:239:PR #320 added read-only `./ns pr-cleanup` classification for stale and relevant open PRs. The command classifies Dependabot PRs, active feature PRs, release-prep PRs, stale docs finalization PRs, superseded docs finalization PRs, conflicting relevant PRs, and safe-to-close PRs without mutating GitHub or Git state.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:410:docs/STATUS.md:243:v0.3.23 is released and post-release verified with Zenodo version DOI `10.5281/zenodo.20261956`. DOI metadata is recorded on main via PR #325. The release completed the deterministic control-workflow hardening line: shared control states, target-state-aware slice runner, safer release-prep/gate/publish flow, evidence cleanup, finalize-guard outcome classification, PR cleanup classification, and the safe patch script helper.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:411:docs/STATUS.md:253:- In progress: agent command inbox slice adds `./ns agent-next` so routine local handoff can pull and execute exactly one pending repo-backed command.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:412:docs/STATUS.md:254:- Completed: PR #336 added inbox-based ./ns agent-next so routine local handoff can pull and execute exactly one pending repo-backed command pair.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:413:docs/planning/NO_COPY_NS_WORKFLOW_CONTROL.md:14:The repository already has `./ns`, `./ns go`, `./ns up`, `agentic-kit workflow ...`, and a shared Cockpit Action Registry. In practice, long ad-hoc terminal blocks still caused quoting and heredoc failures. The latest failure showed that `./ns go` currently delegates to `agentic-kit workflow go`, which uses `.agentic/current_work.yaml` and may execute `git_pull_ff_only`. That is unsafe or unsuitable for active feature branches with local slice work.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:414:docs/planning/NO_COPY_NS_WORKFLOW_CONTROL.md:50:The `./ns dev`, `./ns go`, and `./ns up` concepts should remain representable as Cockpit Actions with safety classes and command metadata. The GUI should eventually display these actions using the shared action registry rather than reimplementing command logic.
docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:416:docs/workflow/REPO_COMMAND_RUNNER.md:39:`./ns agent-next` is the preferred command for routine no-copy handoff. It pulls the current branch, expects exactly one complete pending command pair under `.agentic/commands/inbox/`, copies that pair to the transient `current.yaml` and `current.sh` compatibility path, executes it through `agent-run`, then removes the transient current files.
