docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:533:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:539:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:279:- Terminal handoff rule: future larger runs should commit and push `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`; after PASS, `d` is sufficient unless the run failed or the final status is dirty.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:534:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:540:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:304:Merged PR #375 added `./ns terminal-finalize`, backed by `agentic_project_kit.terminal_logging.finalize_terminal_log(...)`, plus tests and documentation. The safe terminal evidence pattern is now `/tmp` log first, finalize into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`, then stage, commit, and push. Do not commit a repo terminal log while the current process is still writing to it.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:537:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:545:docs/STATUS.md:272:PR #375 added the terminal log finalization guard. Long terminal runs should tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. Finalization rejects active repo-log sources and logs without an explicit PASS, FAIL, or PENDING result marker.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:541:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:549:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:542:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:550:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:543:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:551:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:54:Do not commit a repository log file while the current process is still writing to it. Long scripts must tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. The finalized log must contain an explicit `### RESULT: PASS ###`, `### RESULT: FAIL ###`, or `### RESULT: PENDING ###` marker.
