docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:1231:docs/reports/terminal/20260519-083856_diagnose-release-version-source-hardening.log:104:docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:394:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:191:The release workflow has been hardened against recurring deterministic failures. The important fixes are: stale dist artifacts are removed before release builds, publish waits for the asynchronous GitHub Release workflow instead of failing immediately, completed releases are verified through ./ns release-verify VERSION, and repeated release checks should no longer treat an already published version as a normal release-gate target.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:1232:docs/reports/terminal/20260519-083856_diagnose-release-version-source-hardening.log:105:docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:396:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:265:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is complete and merged on main. The important completed fixes are: shared `control_state` model, stop-on-fail Python slice-runner core, documented workflow control contract, target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop `./ns release-gate` when release metadata is missing, and automated `./ns release-prep` metadata updates for pyproject, package `__version__`, CITATION, CHANGELOG, README, STATUS, and CURRENT_HANDOFF. Next safe direction: use the new control model to harden dirty-evidence cleanup, finalize-guard machine-readable outcomes, and stale PR cleanup classification before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:1233:docs/reports/terminal/20260519-083856_diagnose-release-version-source-hardening.log:106:docs/reports/terminal/parametrized_git_release_actions_inspection_20260518.log:408:docs/STATUS.md:233:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is integrated on main. The release/PR/finalization workflow now has a shared deterministic control model with machine-readable target states, a stop-on-fail slice runner core, documented control-state semantics, a target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop release-gate behavior when release metadata is missing, and automated release metadata preparation in `./ns release-prep`. This addresses the recurring standard-error class where already reached target states, retryable pending states, or failed core patches caused misleading follow-up failures.
