docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2491:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:712:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:166:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:205:`./ns up` now handles no-op branches idempotently: if no PR exists and the branch has no commits ahead of main, the command reports a clean completion state instead of failing. This is part of the deterministic cleanup of recurring workflow false failures.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2492:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:713:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:175:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:233:The ./ns workflow now includes a commit-guard helper that prevents accidental direct commits and PR attempts from main. If invoked on main, it stops with an instructional failure instead of allowing a non-PR direct-main path. This is part of the current standard-error cleanup before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2493:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:714:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:179:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:248:`./ns finalize-guard <branch> [marker-text]` is now available to inspect finalization branches before attempting PR creation or cleanup. Use it when a docs finalization branch may already be merged, superseded, conflicting, or effectively represented on main. This is part of the standard-error cleanup path before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2496:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:717:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:183:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:265:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is complete and merged on main. The important completed fixes are: shared `control_state` model, stop-on-fail Python slice-runner core, documented workflow control contract, target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop `./ns release-gate` when release metadata is missing, and automated `./ns release-prep` metadata updates for pyproject, package `__version__`, CITATION, CHANGELOG, README, STATUS, and CURRENT_HANDOFF. Next safe direction: use the new control model to harden dirty-evidence cleanup, finalize-guard machine-readable outcomes, and stale PR cleanup classification before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2497:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:718:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:184:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:267:Evidence-cleanup guard is merged on main via PR #316. `./ns clean-evidence` is available and `./ns up` now gives a concrete repair hint for workflow-evidence dirtiness. Next safe standard-error hardening target: make `./ns finalize-guard` return clear machine-readable outcomes such as PASS_ALREADY_ON_MAIN, PASS_NOOP_BRANCH, PASS_SUPERSEDED, FAIL_CONFLICT_RELEVANT, and FAIL_NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW.
