docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2680:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:901:docs/reports/terminal/persistent_handoff_state_inspection_20260518.log:506:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:33:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2681:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:902:docs/reports/terminal/persistent_handoff_state_inspection_20260518.log:508:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:40:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2732:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:953:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:538:README.md:282:The workflow uses `.agentic/workflow_state` and `.agentic/current_work.yaml`. `IDLE` with `current_work.yaml` state `READY` is a safe no-op. A run starts only after an explicit request. The explicit two-step form is `agentic-kit workflow request`, followed by `agentic-kit workflow run`. The shortcut `agentic-kit workflow go` performs the same request-and-run handoff for one bounded workflow step. Guided inspection commands include `agentic-kit workflow state`, `agentic-kit workflow list`, and `agentic-kit workflow show`. A requested run captures bounded local evidence, resets the request to `READY`, updates `docs/reports/CURRENT_WORKFLOW_OUTPUT.md`, uploads a temporary evidence branch, and waits for explicit cleanup. When bounded local output already exists and should be uploaded without pasted terminal output, use `agentic-kit workflow upload-output`, `agentic-kit workflow upload`, or the repo-local shortcut `./ns upload` / `./ns up`. For daily local use, `./ns state`, `./ns list`, `./ns show`, `./ns run`, `./ns go`, `./ns up`, and `./ns fail` provide the short workflow surface. The optional `./ns-menu` helper wraps the same repo-local shortcuts in a simple numbered terminal menu for interactive local use. By default it no longer clears the terminal between menu renders; set `NS_MENU_CLEAR=1` to restore screen clearing. The menu also exposes `./ns actions --json` for the schema-versioned cockpit action inventory.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2733:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:954:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:549:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:2734:docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:955:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:550:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
