docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:3656:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:54:Do not commit a repository log file while the current process is still writing to it. Long scripts must tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. The finalized log must contain an explicit `### RESULT: PASS ###`, `### RESULT: FAIL ###`, or `### RESULT: PENDING ###` marker.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_standard_error_contract_prep.log:3769:docs/TEST_GATES.md:290:A final `### RESULT: PASS ###` is valid only when `WORK RESULT: PASS`, `OVERALL RESULT: PASS`, and, for relevant workflows, `REMOTE_EVIDENCE: PASS` are all true. A previous inner FAIL must not be converted into a final PASS by a later commit or push of evidence. Evidence success and work success are separate outcomes.
