docs/architecture/LOCAL_COCKPIT_FOUNDATION.md:9:The local cockpit is the planned control layer for professional single-user project operation. It should reduce fragile copy-and-paste workflows by exposing structured, inspectable project actions that can be reused by the CLI, shell entrypoints, menus, and a later Tkinter UI.
docs/architecture/LOCAL_COCKPIT_FOUNDATION.md:13:The v0.3.14 foundation introduced a shared action inventory and a central cockpit status command. The v0.3.15 action layer adds explicit execution for registered `read_only` actions while keeping bounded actions blocked unless explicitly allowed and destructive actions blocked. It does not execute destructive git, release, or cleanup actions.
