docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:1:diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:10:+The workflow uses `.agentic/workflow_state` and `.agentic/current_work.yaml`. `IDLE` with `current_work.yaml` state `READY` is a safe no-op. A run starts only after an explicit request. The explicit two-step form is `agentic-kit workflow request`, followed by `agentic-kit workflow run`. The shortcut `agentic-kit workflow go` performs the same request-and-run handoff for one bounded workflow step. A requested run captures bounded local evidence, resets the request to `READY`, updates `docs/reports/CURRENT_WORKFLOW_OUTPUT.md`, uploads a temporary evidence branch, and waits for explicit cleanup. When bounded local output already exists and should be uploaded without pasted terminal output, use `agentic-kit workflow upload-output` or the repo-local shortcut `./ns upload`.
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:14:diff --git a/docs/DOCUMENTATION_COVERAGE.yaml b/docs/DOCUMENTATION_COVERAGE.yaml
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:27:diff --git a/docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md b/docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:33: After adding those aliases to `~/.zshrc`, routine compatibility-entrypoint work becomes:
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:35:+```zsh
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:42: ```zsh
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:58:+`agentic-kit workflow go` is the normal shortcut for the chat-assisted workflow: it sets `.agentic/current_work.yaml` to `state: REQUESTED` and runs one bounded workflow step. It replaces the routine manual sequence `workflow request` plus `workflow run` without removing either explicit command. `agentic-kit workflow upload-output` uploads the latest bounded local workflow evidence for review, so terminal output does not need to be pasted into chat when a local evidence file exists.
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:62: `agentic-kit workflow status` reports both state layers. Add `--explain` for a read-only interpretation and recommended next step. The explanation must remain read-only: for dirty working trees and failed workflow states it should recommend inspection before any workflow automation. For example:
docs/reports/evidence_upload_shortcuts_mvp_diff.md:65: - dirty working tree: inspect `git status` before running workflow automation.
