docs/reports/terminal/20260519-091311_mandatory-terminal-evidence-capture-diagnosis.log:323:docs/STATUS.md:100:As of PR #423, the repo-backed no-copy workflow is the active bridge toward the local GUI. Remote tasks are queued under `.agentic/commands/inbox/`, local execution runs through `./ns agent-next`, and durable evidence is written under `docs/reports/command_runs/` and `docs/reports/terminal/`. The current hardening includes command-run pointers, terminal-log pointers, result-footers for `p`/`f`/paste-output decisions, missing-current-script report robustness, inner fail-marker detection, communication artifact garbage collection, and `./ns command-inbox-check` rejecting completed command ids that remain pending.
