docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1056:docs/STATUS.md:18:The immediate goal after v0.3.29 is to close out v0.3.30 GUI readiness hardening. This is not a Tkinter implementation slice. The release line hardens the machine-readable contracts a later thin Tkinter cockpit will consume: action results, cockpit JSON output, registry-only action selection, command queue state, and evidence state.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1057:docs/STATUS.md:24:v0.3.34 is planned as the final pre-GUI portable-core hardening line before starting the thin Tkinter cockpit implementation.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1058:docs/STATUS.md:26:Goal: move the remaining risky release, DOI, evidence, PR-closeout, and typed-work-order control logic out of large shell blocks and into tested Python core functions that can be called by CLI, `./ns`, typed work orders, and the later Tkinter cockpit.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1059:docs/STATUS.md:34:- Provide machine-readable results or stable action result objects for GUI-relevant actions.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1060:docs/STATUS.md:38:Tkinter remains explicitly deferred until this portable-core hardening baseline is released and post-release verified.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1061:docs/STATUS.md:40:Acceptance criteria for starting the Tkinter cockpit after v0.3.34:
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1062:docs/STATUS.md:45:- GUI-facing actions can be invoked without composing fragile multi-step shell scripts.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1063:docs/STATUS.md:57:The active bridge toward the local GUI is no-copy/evidence governance and communication artifact GC hardening, not hidden automation. Normal PASS/FAIL handoff should rely on committed and pushed reports. Manual paste-output is reserved for hard failures such as authentication problems, network failures, terminal crashes, missing remote evidence, or workflow-level ambiguity.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1064:docs/STATUS.md:59:Communication artifact GC hardening is now part of the pre-GUI baseline: symlinked transient artifacts are rejected, repo evidence and command inbox files are protected, and local /tmp/agentic-project-kit-*.log cleanup is TTL-based and dry-run-first via ./ns artifact-gc --tmp-logs.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1065:docs/STATUS.md:63:v0.3.32 is the release-phase-semantics and evidence-closeout hardening line. It does not ship the Tkinter GUI.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1066:docs/STATUS.md:99:Finish v0.3.30 by documenting and gating the GUI readiness hardening baseline, then prepare the v0.3.30 release. Do not start Tkinter in this release line. The first thin Tkinter cockpit belongs after the v0.3.30 contracts are released and verified.
docs/reports/terminal/v0.3.36_final_pre_release_readiness_check.log:1067:docs/STATUS.md:101:Do not expand Pattern Advisor, release automation, or hidden command selection before the GUI foundation and planning freshness guards are stable.
